CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Teen-Queen Contestants - These fourteen young misses of the Hill District are vying for the title Teen-Queen in the annual contest sponsored by Hill City.  They are, left to right:...Elizabeth Sharpe and Joan Roberts"
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Elizabeth Sharpe wearing light colored blouse with rounded collar and string bow at neck, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of Joan Roberts wearing light colored patterned blouse with bow at neck, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest
